ted from various components within the information system (e.g., module or policy filter).\n\nWhen a user logs on, the auid is set to the uid of the account being authenticated. Daemons are not user sessions and have the loginuid set to -1. The auid representation is an unsigned 32-bit integer, which equals 4294967295. The audit system interprets -1, 4294967295, and \"unset\" in the same way.\n\nThe system call rules are loaded into a matching engine that intercepts each system call made by all programs on the system. Therefore, it is very important to use system call rules only when absolutely necessary since these affect performance. The more rules, the bigger the performance hit. The performance can be helped, however, by combining system calls into one rule whenever possible.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015, SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020, SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031, SRG-OS-000392-GPOS-00172, SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000130","CCI-000135","CCI-000169","CCI-000172","CCI-002884"],"reference_identifier":"7449","uuid":"fa07bb26-5c7d-4eee-be0a-797837f0afea","stig_uuid":"b8557813-66ea-4f19-a926-47e0ebc5272c","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-RHEL9_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 41E9FC4AA27374F9955F49C9AA7284741A2508A2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'RHEL 9 must audit all uses of the userhelper command.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the RHEL 9 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-258209","group_tree":[{"id":"V-258209","title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-258209","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000037-GPOS-00015","